sec.p:
Systematic and thematic content analysis was applied as data were concurrently collected and analyzed using the constant comparative method. The following steps describe the employed process:


Listening to the recorded interviews and repeated reading of the recorded audio files and notes;



Interviews were transcribed verbatim and saved in Word 2003 and One Note application format;



Data from field notes were analyzed and integrated;



Semantic units or content areas were determined;



Data from interviews, FGD and field observations were collected and tabulated to obtain a general idea about the contents;



Data were coded by two independent reviewers;



Categorized data were coded based on similarities;



Major themes and sub-themes were identified.
